Despite these challenges, there are several steps that could be taken to improve the situation:
- Increase access to paid family leave by expanding eligibility criteria beyond just those working full-time jobs;
- Create tax incentives for employers who offer more generous parental leave benefits;
- Encourage flexible work schedules so parents can balance caregiving responsibilities with career goals;
- Invest in high quality childcare options so parents feel confident leaving their babies with someone else while they work;
